Method 1: Edit Document (Recommended)
-------------------------------------
1. Go to MongoDB Atlas → Database → Browse Collections
2. Select "users" collection  
3. Filter: { "email": "abhi.storage36@gmail.com" }
4. Click "Edit Document" button
5. Add/update these fields:
   - notificationFrequency: "1min"
   - notificationsEnabled: true
   - notificationStartHour: 7
   - notificationEndHour: 8
6. Click "Update"

Method 2: Update Query
---------------------
Run this update query in Atlas:

db.users.updateOne(
  { "email": "abhi.storage36@gmail.com" },
  { 
    $set: {
      "notificationFrequency": "1min",
      "notificationsEnabled": true,
      "notificationStartHour": 7,
      "notificationEndHour": 8,
      "dailyGoal": 2000,
      "defaultWaterAmount": 250
    }
  }
)

